-1811482765.text: "The catalytic PI3K isoforms can be regulated by receptor tyrosine kinases and/or G protein coupled receptors and activate AKT, serum and glucocorticoid regulated kinase (SGK), phosphoinositide dependent kinase 1 (PDK1), mammalian target of rapamycin (mTOR), and several other pathways that control a variety of cellular processes including proliferation, growth, apoptosis, migration, and metabolism 5."
